fields.Title: WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE MAIN
fields.Description:
Meeting Klaasje again, on the roof
0) Intro
1) Your name and 
2) why u here? (orbs and drugs from room) 
3) Wildflower
5) did you hear me night before / last time we saw
6) Looking for Ruby

fields.Title: Empathy: "That must be her tell: the cigarett..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That must be her tell: the cigarette. It hurts her to look directly at the corpse so she reverts her gaze to you.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "No need to dilly-dally. She's tough..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No need to dilly-dally. She's tough.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I can see that." She nods. "I'm gl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can see that." She nods. "I'm glad all this *onward going* has brought you to me."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's okay, it's absolutely okay to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's okay, it's absolutely okay to be that." She nods compassionately. "What is this about, officers?"

fields.Title: You: ""No. Not wow." (Lean in.) "I am the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. Not wow." (Lean in.) "I am the most boring cop in the world now. Nothing like *that* will ever happen again."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I very much doubt that. What bring..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I very much doubt that. What brings this *so-called* boring cop back to me?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Wow..." Vapour rises from her coff..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow..." Vapour rises from her coffee cup. "Can it be stopped? And if not, what are we to do with the time left?"

fields.Title: You: ""So you were the most beautiful?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you were the most beautiful?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's okay. This is just him being..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's okay. This is just him being a scintillating wordsmith. I'm used to it."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm pretty sure I have the legal r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm pretty sure I have the legal right to demand your passport, miss."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Why else?" He's suddenly very atte..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why else?" He's suddenly very attentive.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I'm an unpopular girl." She takes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm an unpopular girl." She takes a drag. "There are people back home who don't like me -- if they show up, I'm in a *hurry*."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I would *love* to change the subje..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I would *love* to change the subject. It's not important. Unless I'm some kind of... suspect?" She arches an eyebrow.

fields.Title: Drama: "She seems to be telling the truth,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She seems to be telling the truth, sire.

fields.Title: Composure: "If any of this made her nervous, it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If any of this made her nervous, it certainly doesn't show in her expression or her movements.

fields.Title: You: ""What are you doing here -- in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you doing here -- in the Whirling-in-Rags?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "That *yeah* is the kind that consol..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That *yeah* is the kind that consoles and sweeps under the rug at the same time.

fields.Title: You: ""Doesn't feel like love at all.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't feel like love at all."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Are you sure? Love is *terror*..."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you sure? Love is *terror*..." She breathes in a large billow of menthol-infused smoke, savours it, then lets it out slowly.

fields.Title: You: ""Understood.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Understood."

fields.Title: You: ""When was it changed? During your s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "When was it changed? During your stay?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She nods, inspecting your sideburns..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She nods, inspecting your sideburns. "You've got it bad as it is."

fields.Title: You: ""Then tell the truth.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then tell the truth."

fields.Title: Half Light: "She feels like quarry, encircled......"
fields.Dialogue Text: She feels like quarry, encircled... Her eyes dart to the door.

fields.Title: You: ""It could be connected.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It could be connected."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""For my *sins* of course. The long..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "For my *sins* of course. The long standing sins of a bad, frivolous person."

fields.Title: You: ""Can you tell me more about Lely, t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can you tell me more about Lely, the hanged man? My partner needs to hear this."
fields.Alternate1: "I have a couple of more questions about the deceased."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Her eyes widen. "Oh...""
fields.Dialogue Text: Her eyes widen. "Oh..."

fields.Title: You: ""Did you take the documents?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did you take the documents?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""With money, sir." She takes a drag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "With money, sir." She takes a drag. "It's not exactly the Antistar-sized caboodle I intend for it to be one day, but it's getting there."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Sure," she smiles. "Onto where?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure," she smiles. "Onto where?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Good luck, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good luck, officer."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Now she's trapped here, in the cage..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now she's trapped here, in the cage -- just like you.

fields.Title: You: ""There are vortices of dark energy..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There are vortices of dark energy present, but not to Hell -- to another place. A *third* place, much different from our world."

fields.Title: Composure: "She tries to look indifferent, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She tries to look indifferent, but still has to take a drag of her cigarette -- so as not to flinch.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's much nicer now." Her eyes wan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's much nicer now." Her eyes wander north, toward the yard...

fields.Title: Empathy: "This does not come as good news to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This does not come as good news to him.

fields.Title: You: ""I've found something more *downbea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've found something more *downbeat* for my next appearance." (Whip out the tape of "Smallest Church")

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Ah, I see." She takes a pensive dr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, I see." She takes a pensive drag of her menthol cigarette.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""That's the one! The Small Sad Chur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's the one! The Small Sad Church Song! I've missed it, I really have."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "We'll show him. You'll tear it up A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We'll show him. You'll tear it up ALL the styles!

fields.Title: Endurance: "No. She reached the end of her elas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. She reached the end of her elasticity about two months ago -- from here on out, every chip and knick and blow stays in there somewhere.

fields.Title: Authority: "Do *not* go along with this."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do *not* go along with this.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Why not? You're a powerhouse."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why not? You're a powerhouse.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Doesn't matter! The flow of events..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Doesn't matter! The flow of events is already passing you by! The woman said something, now the man's saying something... KEEP YOUR HEAD IN THE GAME, SON!

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Officer." She nods to you in greet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer." She nods to you in greeting. "It's a fine day for questions."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Wanna hear what's stupid? Somewhere..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wanna hear what's stupid? Somewhere in a one room apartment on Boogie Street a young man shows Patrol Officer Tillbrook his genital warts, asking if they're *cancer*.

fields.Title: You: ""Revacholian literature too?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Revacholian literature too?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Cool." She looks at the white cent..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool." She looks at the white cents in your hand. "I've made more money by just *being* than I have with Oranjese lit."

fields.Title: You: ""What is Miss Oranje '37?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is Miss Oranje '37?"

fields.Title: Logic: "She was 14 at the time."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was 14 at the time.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Well-well." She leans back. "It se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well-well." She leans back. "It seems I either underestimated you -- or overestimated your hangover, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""No, that was *sincere*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, that was *sincere*."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""No, I'm not." She waves you off."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I'm not." She waves you off.

fields.Title: You: ""I hate objects. I am part of the A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I hate objects. I am part of the Anti-Object Task Force."

fields.Title: You: ""It's a feeling. White and filled w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a feeling. White and filled with doom. Gaseous. Invisible. Deadly. It's everywhere."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I always wanted to see 'The Only C..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I always wanted to see 'The Only City in the World' in the worst time of the year. It's a tourist thing."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It is." She moves slightly to your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is." She moves slightly to your left to check her reflection in it.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Question avoided. Let's conclude th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Question avoided. Let's conclude that she has admirers. Plenty of them.

fields.Title: You: ""There's a peep hole on the other s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a peep hole on the other side, looking into your bedroom."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Okay..." There's a pause as she pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay..." There's a pause as she processes this information.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I did not." She takes a drag of he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I did not." She takes a drag of her cigarette. "Do you think this has something to do with what happened?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes. Looking into your bedroom, mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Looking into your bedroom, miss." The lieutenant points to her window. The unmade bed is visible through the glass.

fields.Title: You: ""Let's not discuss it any longer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's not discuss it any longer."

fields.Title: Drama: "Pff... It's surely an act. Ask ques..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pff... It's surely an act. Ask questions. Tough ones, preferably.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm afraid you may be in danger.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm afraid you may be in danger."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She thinks for a moment, then shrug..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She thinks for a moment, then shrugs. "Yes, I am -- regardless of who took the documents."

fields.Title: You: ""I'll file this under a *theft* of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'll file this under a *theft* of some kind."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""You mentioned sea water? I was wor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mentioned sea water? I was worried I'd been too careless with the latch. The documents were probably," she waves her cigarette, "just washed away..."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Miss Oranje? Now there is something..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Miss Oranje? Now there is something you should *linger* on.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Best of luck to you, officers.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Best of luck to you, officers."

fields.Title: You: ""Ruby is definitely not at her old..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ruby is definitely not at her old crash pad anymore."

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""Now that Kim isn't here -- let's t..."]
You: ""Nice view you've got here.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nice view you've got here."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "...then toned over several years of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...then toned over several years of self-defence training. You can sense it in the sharp pointing of her elbows.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Have I ever... This is the fabled..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have I ever... This is the fabled Cop of the Apocalypse."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I can see that." She takes a sip...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can see that." She takes a sip. "It suits you."

fields.Title: You: ""You have? Why?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You have? Why?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The Small Sad Church Song tells it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Small Sad Church Song tells it like it is, detective -- *sad*."

fields.Title: You: ""I would like to withdraw the comme..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I would like to withdraw the comment I made earlier. Given the situation we find ourselves in now, it seems out of place."

fields.Title: You: ""Say nothing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Say nothing."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Wow." She turns to the lieutenant...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow." She turns to the lieutenant. "What brings *The Phoenix* back to me?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm disappointed it's dragging out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm disappointed it's dragging out like this. What a farce..." (Look around.)

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Yeah, man." Her face wrinkles into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, man." Her face wrinkles into a rock 'n' roll smile.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Of lilacs and lightning." She squi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of lilacs and lightning." She squints her eyes as if to see them in the distance. "Parks, glass, duraluminium -- Vredefort is a conference city. It's always autumn there. And night. At least it was for me."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""That's just a phase the Revacholia..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's just a phase the Revacholian hero goes through..." She breathes in the menthol-flavoured fumes, savouring it...

fields.Title: You: ""Back to you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Back to you."

fields.Title: You: ""What is a beauty pageant?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is a beauty pageant?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's a competition." She takes a d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a competition." She takes a drag. "For stupid girls. Men look at them and choose the most beautiful."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Another innocent tradition bulldoze..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Another innocent tradition bulldozed by the march of ethical *progress*!

fields.Title: You: ""No. I've just come to talk.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I've just come to talk."
fields.Alternate1: "No. We've just come to talk."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Not too hard. You told us about th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not too hard. You told us about the investigation Friday night. Downstairs. At a table full of local kids and dockworkers. You told pretty much everyone. After you showed them your gun..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Whooh..." She wipes her brow."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whooh..." She wipes her brow.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""That's pretty hard core," she nods..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's pretty hard core," she nods. "I'm part of the Anti-Human Task Force myself."

fields.Title: You: "(Nod.) "Anyway.""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Nod.) "Anyway."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "This is by far not the only reason..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is by far not the only reason she's here -- and she isn't really hiding it, either.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "An evasive manoeuvre. Ask a follow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An evasive manoeuvre. Ask a follow up!

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Yeah... I'm trying not to lie to y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah... I'm trying not to lie to you here. Stop making it hard."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay then -- I'll cut you some sla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay then -- I'll cut you some slack."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The truth is I'm a horrible girl...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The truth is I'm a horrible girl. Windows break around me. It's not their fault."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I really don't know, sir." She tak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I really don't know, sir." She takes a sip of her cold coffee. "I certainly don't *feel* like I've won. I feel like shit, sir. All the time."

fields.Title: You: ""That's it then, I guess." (Conclud..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's it then, I guess." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: You: ""It all seems fortuitous -- for you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It all seems fortuitous -- for you."

fields.Title: You: ""Does that happen to you often?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Does that happen to you often?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The Antistar is (or was) a Vesperti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The Antistar is (or was) a Vespertine rock and roll star, who liked to do drugs. He did so many drugs he eventually mutated -- into a corpse.

fields.Title: You: ""It's a word. Let's get on with it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a word. Let's get on with it."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "There may be more to this *mystery*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There may be more to this *mystery* -- at some later time. She's holding back. Let's make a mental note for now.

fields.Title: You: ""If it was recent, who do you think..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If it was recent, who do you think made it -- Ruby?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""...At any rate, the suspect isn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...At any rate, the suspect isn't there anymore."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I really don't know what to tell y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I really don't know what to tell you..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Now, I'm no expert on cops, but th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now, I'm no expert on cops, but that sounds like one special police officer to me."

fields.Title: You: ""Now that Kim isn't here -- let's t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now that Kim isn't here -- let's talk about Sunday night."
fields.Alternate1: "Let's talk about Sunday night again -- the sounds from my room."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["TASK.hear_what_sunday_night"]  and  IsKimHere() == false  and  Variable["TASK.hear_what_sunday_night_done"] == false

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant gives you a little l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant gives you a little look.

fields.Title: You: ""Know that I am no longer the Cop o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Know that I am no longer the Cop of the Apocalypse. The prophecy was wrong. The signs meant nothing. The hangover has passed."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Nice? I don't know about that, off..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nice? I don't know about that, officer..." She looks north, toward the yard.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Like riding a 'copocycle.'" She ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like riding a 'copocycle.'" She takes a sip of her coffee.

fields.Title: You: ""You ain't seen nothing yet. There'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You ain't seen nothing yet. There's a *karaoke* stage downstairs."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: IsTaskActive("TASK.sing_karaoke")  and  CheckItem("music_smallest_church_tape") == false  and  IsKimHere() == true--[[ Variable[ ]]

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She tilts her head to the side and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She tilts her head to the side and smiles. Vapour rises from her coffee cup.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""A penitent cop-monk..." she says t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A penitent cop-monk..." she says to herself. "What brings this *changed man* to me?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Wow, there are *copotypes*..." Vap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow, there are *copotypes*..." Vapour rises from the coffee cup in her hand.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "The victim's ethnicity *could* have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The victim's ethnicity *could* have been Oranjese... -- something for later?

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Thankfully -- it's implied."
fields.Dialogue Text: Thankfully -- it's implied.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's not very cool, but what can y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not very cool, but what can you do?"

fields.Title: You: "(Lower your thumb.) "I disapprove o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Lower your thumb.) "I disapprove of this custom."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's okay, he's just getting his b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's okay, he's just getting his bearings. The world of beauty pageants *is* bewildering."

fields.Title: You: ""Why?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why?"

fields.Title: You: ""How do I know you've told us your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How do I know you've told us your real name?"

fields.Title: You: ""Not yet.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not yet."

fields.Title: You: ""You might be.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You might be."

fields.Title: You: ""What exactly is the nature of this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What exactly is the nature of this 'Contamination'?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Somewhere below, military-grade Sad..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somewhere below, military-grade Sad is dripping off the walls... you should say the first thing. It's honest. It will lead to introspection.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Sounds like an advanced form of wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sounds like an advanced form of what I've got. With a bit of old love sprinkled on top."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Huh. This isn't good.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Huh. This isn't good."

fields.Title: You: ""Looking into your bedroom, miss.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looking into your bedroom, miss."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Do you think this is somehow *conn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you think this is somehow *connected* to me?"

fields.Title: You: ""You're right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right."

fields.Title: You: ""The dried flowers on the roof -- c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The dried flowers on the roof -- could Ruby have left them? These don't fit with anything."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's mostly about the lack of clea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's mostly about the lack of cleaning services. And an abundance of *me*."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She laughs: "There it is again -- m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She laughs: "There it is again -- man of *words*. I can appreciate that."
fields.Alternate1: She laughs. "There it is again -- man of *words*. I can appreciate that, having half a bachelor's degree in words and all..."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, I know about the *crash pad*...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I know about the *crash pad*. Even spoke to the land lady. But Ruby's not there anymore."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""That doesn't surprise me... She's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That doesn't surprise me... She's careful. But -- before you ask -- I really have no clue where she could've gone."

fields.Title: Empathy: "There is something in her light bro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is something in her light brown eyes... a sadness. When she thinks about the death of that man.

fields.Title: You: ""Hell? You know not of which you sp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hell? You know not of which you speak!"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I know." She smiles with her eyebr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know." She smiles with her eyebrows. "That's *probably* also why the cleaning lady quit."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "YOU'LL SOUND LIKE A NAMBY-PAMBY!"
fields.Dialogue Text: YOU'LL SOUND LIKE A NAMBY-PAMBY!

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Wow..." She shakes her head in sil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow..." She shakes her head in silent disbelief, breathing in the coffee smell.

fields.Title: You: ""Johnny Law is about to tear it up...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Johnny Law is about to tear it up. Sad-style."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes. *Wow*." (Lean in.) "I am now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. *Wow*." (Lean in.) "I am now a herald of the Planetary Slaughterhouse. The Abattoir To Come."

fields.Title: You: ""Know that I am no longer the Cop o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Know that I am no longer the Cop of the Apocalypse. The prophecy was wrong. The signs meant nothing. The hangover has passed."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "It's about DEDICATION, son. That an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's about DEDICATION, son. That and you're *probably* a gym teacher. Only a former gym teacher can think these thoughts and drink so much.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""A bad memory, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "A bad memory, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""What's that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's that?"

fields.Title: You: ""I have no intention of doing that.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have no intention of doing that."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""That's the natural state of the Re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's the natural state of the Revacholian hero..." She breathes in the menthol flavoured fumes, savouring it -- then breathes out.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "...then breathes out. "Before they..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...then breathes out. "Before they plunge into full-core humanity- and world-saving."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "What about Revacholian literature?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What about Revacholian literature? People sometimes reveal things about themselves when they discuss such matters...

fields.Title: Empathy: "Her voice is indifferent to the num..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her voice is indifferent to the number.

fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm Kim Kitsuragi." The lieutenant steps in. "I'm a detective from Precinct 57. I see you've already met my colleague."

fields.Title: You: ""That is unimportant to the case at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That is unimportant to the case at hand."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""You're doing just fine -- after al..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're doing just fine -- after all, your path has led you back to me."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I assure you, he is not about to t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I assure you, he is not about to tear it up in *any* style. In fact..."

fields.Title: You: ""No comment.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No comment."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Oh, I've got a couple of good year..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, I've got a couple of good years left on my warranty..." She looks down at her body shimmering in the silver jumpsuit.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Questions? What about?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Questions? What about?"

fields.Title: You: ""What is your name, miss? For the r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is your name, miss? For the record."
fields.Alternate1: "Can I ask more about you? For the record."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I doubt you will succeed." She sha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I doubt you will succeed." She shakes her head. "So, what is this about, officers?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The Republic of Oranje is a democra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The Republic of Oranje is a democratic nation on the Mundi isola, north of here, over the sea and across the pale. It is one of the six major Occidental nations to hold stake in the continued occupation of Revachol (the Coalition). People consider it a *reasonable* superpower.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: ""He's warm," Mollins replies, "beca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's warm," Mollins replies, "because he's under the radiator."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Cool." She looks at the black note..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool." She looks at the black note in your hand. "I've made more money by just *being* than I have with Oranjese lit."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""'The record' -- so official!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "'The record' -- so official!"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Love is terror." She breathes in a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Love is terror." She breathes in a large billow of menthol-infused smoke, savours it, then lets it out slowly...

fields.Title: You: ""What happened to the old New World?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What happened to the old New World?"

fields.Title: You: ""What's funky?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's funky?"

fields.Title: You: ""Any admirers, miss?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Any admirers, miss?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She keeps looking at the door with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She keeps looking at the door with a worried expression. The wind ruffles her hair.

fields.Title: Logic: "Yet? Maybe it's something she's kee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yet? Maybe it's something she's keeping for a later move, when she's more sure of herself...

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Clearly, I haven't. We're having t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Clearly, I haven't. We're having this conversation, aren't we? How *well* could it have gone. I mean... " She looks around.

fields.Title: Empathy: "He feels uncomfortable with this co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He feels uncomfortable with this conversation. He doesn't know what to add.

fields.Title: You: "Look up to the grey sky."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look up to the grey sky.
fields.tooltip2: Snowing. Try again when it's stopped.
fields.tooltip3: Raining. Try again when it's stopped.

fields.Title: You: ""Let's talk more about this so-call..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's talk more about this so-called assault."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Oh my god, now it's turning into N..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh my god, now it's turning into Narco Mania. It's got to be serious if it's *two words*."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""No-no! You said *narcomania*. What..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no! You said *narcomania*. What kind of word is that?"

fields.Title: You: ""I can't seem to find Ruby. Do you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't seem to find Ruby. Do you have any idea where she might be?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We found that *crash pad* on the c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We found that *crash pad* on the coast, miss, and even spoke to the land lady. She seemed... rather devoted to the suspect..."

fields.Title: You: ""Is there a cleaning lady? I think..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is there a cleaning lady? I think I *need* one." (Proceed politely.)
fields.Alternate1: "You mentioned a cleaning lady -- I think I need one." (Proceed.)

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "If that's true then *Revacholian li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If that's true then *Revacholian lit* would fit you like a glove.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "It's good we discussed your history..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's good we discussed your history with her, he thinks. I can play along.

fields.Title: You: ""It has.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It has."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Have I ever..." She turns to you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have I ever..." She turns to you. "Have you grown accustomed to your role as a 'police officer'?"

fields.Title: You: ""Hear that, Kim? I am a *huge* deal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hear that, Kim? I am a *huge* deal around here."

fields.Title: You: ""This is part of the... khm... *thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is part of the... khm... *thing* I told you about."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Doesn't matter! The flow of events..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Doesn't matter! The flow of events is passing you by! The woman said something, now the man's saying something... KEEP YOUR HEAD IN THE GAME, SON!

fields.Title: You: ""They tell us you were raped.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "They tell us you were raped."
fields.Alternate1: "They tell us you've been through something difficult."

fields.Title: You: ""Let's return to this later, miss."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's return to this later, miss." [Leave.]
fields.Alternate1: "Let's return to this later." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""What do you do, miss? What is your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you do, miss? What is your *specialization*?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Nothing -- if you're no longer the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing -- if you're no longer there."

fields.Title: You: ""Oranjese lit?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oranjese lit?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Sure." She takes a drag."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure." She takes a drag.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The kind of hurry where you can't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The kind of hurry where you can't afford to *not* find your documents -- but don't worry. This has *nothing* to do with your investigation."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""If I didn't know better, I'd say y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If I didn't know better, I'd say you feigned that 'fuck-having' line to get me to say something stupid. Was that so?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "Oh my..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh my...

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Cool. I think I'm developing a pin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool. I think I'm developing a pinch of that too. It hasn't done wonders to my taste in interior decoration."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Funkytown," she says and takes a s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Funkytown," she says and takes a sip of her coffee.

fields.Title: You: ""You're too young to call yourself..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're too young to call yourself a disco has-been."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She looks at you and nods."
fields.Dialogue Text: She looks at you and nods.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Samaran boxing, or Sam Bo. Graceful..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Samaran boxing, or Sam Bo. Graceful martial arts stuff. 'Sam Bo- style' implies stealth and cool.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Hello again, officer." She sounds..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello again, officer." She sounds tired now. All the pep is gone.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Shit... I don't know. Maybe it's b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shit... I don't know. Maybe it's been there for a long time. Maybe the local kids use it or something. I don't know..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I'm stuck in Martinaise, just like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm stuck in Martinaise, just like all of us. I've been up here for... I don't know how long now? I like to call this my *rooftop containment facility*."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She narrows her eyes. "You mean tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She narrows her eyes. "You mean that little thing you caught -- when you first came here? On the roof there?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Thank you, but actually -- now tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, but actually -- now that I think about it -- you mentioned sea water? I was worried I'd been too careless with the latch mechanism... The documents were probably," she waves her cigarette, "just washed away..."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "All things considered -- very. Now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All things considered -- very. Now linger.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Anyway -- I thought it would be *f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Anyway -- I thought it would be *funny* to say I didn't do it. Because I knew about your investigation..." She cringes. "Does that make me a suspect? I really must stop saying stupid things..."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "It's hard to tell if she means it i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's hard to tell if she means it in earnest or as a joke.

fields.Title: You: ""You seem to have, among other thin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You seem to have, among other things, Preptide."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Thank you, miss." He turns to you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, miss." He turns to you. "We should do a thorough search of the fishing village."
fields.Alternate1: "Thank you, miss." He turns to you. "We should do a more thorough search of the fishing village."

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""I noticed your room is close to mi..."]
You: ""No time for pleasantries. We have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No time for pleasantries. We have questions for you." (Proceed in a rush.)

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Have I ever! This is the biggest f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have I ever! This is the biggest fan of Ostentatious Orchestrations I have seen in my *life*. And I have seen a few..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""'Oh yeah,'" she declares. "'Life g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "'Oh yeah,'" she declares. "'Life gets hard -- but we go on.'"

fields.Title: Authority: "OH YEAH, FEEL THE POWER."
fields.Dialogue Text: OH YEAH, FEEL THE POWER.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That is not actually what a police..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That is not actually what a police siren sounds like." The lieutenant turns to the young woman.

fields.Title: You: ""Those days are behind me. I am her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Those days are behind me. I am here to ask questions."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I stand corrected. What brings you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I stand corrected. What brings you back to me -- the coming apocalypse?"

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "What is there to do now -- stranded..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What is there to do now -- stranded here? The question is personal to her. More than humour.

fields.Title: You: "Wait what? I'm a what?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait what? I'm a what?

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Wasn't the tattoo on the hanged man..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wasn't the tattoo on the hanged man an *Oranjese* Map of the Waterways? The thought begins to form in your head, then dissipates -- something for later.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's the past." She takes a sip of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's the past." She takes a sip of her coffee. "People can't go back to the past."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""No!" She seems glad that you asked..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No!" She seems glad that you asked. "Revacholian lit is about how *magnificent and serious* Revachol is. It's about how you have to save the world."

fields.Title: You: ""I do feel the urge to save the wor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I do feel the urge to save the world, yes. I guess that's why I'm on this case."

fields.Title: You: ""You were 14?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You were 14?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Indeed.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Indeed."

fields.Title: You: ""Cool." (Raise your thumb.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool." (Raise your thumb.)

fields.Title: Shivers: "A squall of seagulls under the low-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A squall of seagulls under the low-hanging sky. Distant machinery from the harbour. It's wide open and cold.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Then she whispers: "I'm just a girl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then she whispers: "I'm just a girl whom windows break around."

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""Titus Hardie gave me a recording...."]
You: ""It's possible.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's possible."

fields.Title: Empathy: "A jitter of fear and disgust moves..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A jitter of fear and disgust moves through her body, beginning from her shoulders and ending in her hips. The cigarette tastes foul to her now.

fields.Title: You: ""What are you contained for then?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you contained for then?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks away, over the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks away, over the railing.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The what?" She narrows her eyes. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The what?" She narrows her eyes. "Oh, those ones! I don't know, sir. I said I have no idea what to make of them. Honestly, I think they're just trash."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Look." She greets you, taking a dr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look." She greets you, taking a drag. "It's dark outside, the dogs are barking and I'm still here, drinking my coffee -- just like I promised." She smiles faintly.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "The young woman cranes her neck, tr..."]
You: ""My working hypothesis is that ther..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My working hypothesis is that there is a cosmic conspiracy of some kind -- and it's out to get us all."

fields.Title: You: ""I have this strange feeling that i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have this strange feeling that it was an undiscovered *cryptid* that took your documents."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Better safe than sorry." She takes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Better safe than sorry." She takes a drag and smiles.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Although -- if I remember correctl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Although -- if I remember correctly -- there are still some centuries to go. Very anticlimactic."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, my copotype is unbelievably r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, my copotype is unbelievably rare."

fields.Title: Composure: "What could she be thinking of? It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What could she be thinking of? It's hard to say -- her shoulders are relaxed, her eyes on the cigarette.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "We should have discussed your histo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We should have discussed your history before we came here, he thinks. So many unpleasant surprises with this guy...

fields.Title: Half Light: "Sheer terror. Panic and screaming."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sheer terror. Panic and screaming.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "She's not angry, but it's true: she..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's not angry, but it's true: she's gonna have to find some more Preptide now.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Ah, I see." She takes a pensive dr..."]
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""A third place? Interesting." She t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A third place? Interesting." She takes a sip of coffee. "That's probably why the cleaning lady quit."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Have I ever... This man has an *un..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have I ever... This man has an *unforgettable* way with words."

fields.Title: You: ""I have grown accustomed to the *po..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have grown accustomed to the *power*, miss."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Ah, I can see that you have, offic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, I can see that you have, officer." She nods.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "No, it wouldn't. It would be themat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, it wouldn't. It would be thematic.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "It's almost imperceptible in the co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's almost imperceptible in the cold wind, but the blood vessels on her cheeks and neck dilate.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, I understood that, officer."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I understood that, officer." He turns to the young woman.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Wow indeed... And what brings this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow indeed... And what brings this herald back to me?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can assure you -- there really,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can assure you -- there really, really are *not*."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I know," she says with great melan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know," she says with great melancholy. "What now?"

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Her birthmarks also signal Oranje...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her birthmarks also signal Oranje. You don't know why, but Oranjese girls tend to come speckled with them.

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's the world's most tired smile."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's the world's most tired smile.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I'm afraid you can't, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm afraid you can't, officer."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Thank you for your candour -- why?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you for your candour -- why?"

fields.Title: You: ""What kind of *people* are these --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What kind of *people* are these -- the ones that don't like you?"
fields.Alternate1: "The people who don't like you -- you mean the ones you're running from, right?"

fields.Title: Logic: "Didn't she say you would have to *i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Didn't she say you would have to *interrogate* her? Before? And that she *didn't do it*? What was up with that?

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The World?" She looks around."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The World?" She looks around.

fields.Title: You: ""It's a demon who smells of betraya..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a demon who smells of betrayal. And apricots."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Betrayed by the things we love --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Betrayed by the things we love -- what a rotten deal..." She breathes in a large billow of menthol-infused smoke, then lets it out slowly...

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know what it is.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know what it is."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I heard this is where the washed u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I heard this is where the washed up disco has-beens go."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""All right." She takes a long, pens..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right." She takes a long, pensive drag of her Astra Menthol.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Thanks." She smiles. It's a sad li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thanks." She smiles. It's a sad little smile, like she's some miniature bird or tiny field mouse.

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: You: ""That's all for now." (Conclude.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's all for now." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: You: ""We don't know at this point.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "We don't know at this point."

fields.Title: You: ""The perforation should be under yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The perforation should be under your bookcase, in your bedroom."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's very hard to believe -- that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's very hard to believe -- that she'd do something like that. But... no. I don't know." She squints. "I just don't know about this, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""But this turned out well for you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But this turned out well for you. You've *slipped* past all suspicions."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""For destroying my first love. For..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "For destroying my first love. For working for bad people. The list goes on and on."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She flashes you a sudden half-smile..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She flashes you a sudden half-smile. "Yes, that must be it. Thank you. I feel better already."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "He's trying to throw her off with t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's trying to throw her off with the bluntness of the question.

fields.Title: You: ""Got it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Got it."

fields.Title: You: ""You have quite the collection of p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You have quite the collection of prescription drugs down there."
fields.Alternate1: "About that drug collection you have down there..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She almost spits out her coffee: "W..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She almost spits out her coffee: "What did you say?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Is that something that happens to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that something that happens to you often, miss?" His tone isn't aggressive, just inquisitive.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Yes, Ruby has her gruff charm.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, Ruby has her gruff charm."

fields.Title: You: ""I guess I should go ask around the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess I should go ask around the fishing village."
fields.Alternate1: "I guess I should go ask around more in the fishing village."

fields.Title: You: ""I noticed your room is close to mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I noticed your room is close to mine. I have a personal question."
fields.Alternate1: "Let's return to Sunday night -- the sounds from my room"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I stand corrected. What brings you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I stand corrected. What brings you back to me -- superstardom?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Of course there are. Look at him....."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course there are. Look at him..." She looks at you, then turns back to the lieutenant. "He is The Phoenix. What brings The Phoenix back to me?"

fields.Title: You: ""Understood, miss.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Understood, miss."

fields.Title: You: ""You're a cop?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're a cop?"

fields.Title: You: ""The world is unimportant -- I want..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The world is unimportant -- I want to hear about you."

fields.Title: You: ""What is beauty?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is beauty?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't think I've ever been 14.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't think I've ever been 14."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Because it's buried in a sealed pl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Because it's buried in a sealed plastic bag at an undisclosed location on the coast. Along with cash and airline tickets."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I don't want to become an indentur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't want to become an indentured servant in a brothel on Boogie Street -- and I don't want my relatives to pay the ransom."

fields.Title: You: ""Why else?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why else?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Okie-dokie." She pours herself mor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okie-dokie." She pours herself more coffee.

fields.Title: You: ""Where does that door lead to?" (Po..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where does that door lead to?" (Point to the door on the roof.)

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Yeaaah..." She draws out the vowel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeaaah..." She draws out the vowel. "I've contaminated it pretty bad."

fields.Title: You: ""Is that why you're out here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that why you're out here?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Don't be alarmed, but Mr. Garte im..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be alarmed, but Mr. Garte implied there's an industrial Sad-spill in there." She taps the roof with her heel.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I'm wintering.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm wintering."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She calculates. "About four months...."

fields.Dialogue Text: Watching herself reflected in the bedroom window -- tall and sparkling and draped in smoke.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Why was there a flower on the roof? I don't know, officer. Because of the wind?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She watches you pocket the petals,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She watches you pocket the petals, then closes her eyes as she breathes in the cigarette fumes...

fields.Title: You: "Look her in the eye."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look her in the eye.
fields.tooltip3: Why did she say she's a suspect?

fields.Title: You: ""It's an old pinball workshop. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an old pinball workshop. The room back there. This place used to be a pinball arcade."

fields.Title: Shivers: "The wet wind, heavy with brine and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The wet wind, heavy with brine and industrial pollution from the stacks nearby, ruffles her hair.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I mean, there's no reason for me t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I mean, there's no reason for me to think they're somehow connected to her."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Lies, I..." She repeats -- then tr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lies, I..." She repeats -- then trails off. It's unclear what she intended to say.

fields.Title: Authority: "Technically, possession of narcotic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Technically, possession of narcotics is legal in Revachol. But you should still reprimand her.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Wow... a hardened, callous highway..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow... a hardened, callous highwayman. Don't think this won't come up again during what will be an opportune moment for me, Officer Disco." She smiles.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Ruby has a gruff charm that inspir..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ruby has a gruff charm that inspires loyalty... I do wish you luck in your search, officer."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Of course she won a beauty pageant...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course she won a beauty pageant. She's very symmetrical.

fields.Title: You: ""No, I just trashed the place.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I just trashed the place."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Thank you for that, officers. Trul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you for that, officers. Truly."

fields.Title: You: ""How long, do you think, until the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How long, do you think, until the hard wears us down?"

fields.Title: You: "I'll go straight to it. I don't wan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'll go straight to it. I don't wanna sound like a namby-pamby.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Good on you, boy. She can take it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good on you, boy. She can take it.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It would, wouldn't it? It would be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It would, wouldn't it? It would be *strange*. You see..."

fields.Title: You: ""What is this wild flower?" (Show h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is this wild flower?" (Show her the flower.)

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Right." She turns to face the wind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." She turns to face the wind, letting it dry her hair.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Same name that Titus gave you. It s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Same name that Titus gave you. It sounds Oranjese -- as does her accent.

fields.Title: You: ""Did you do something wrong?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did you do something wrong?"

fields.Title: You: ""Cool.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool."

fields.Title: You: ""So you were stupid and mediocre?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you were stupid and mediocre?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't think I've ever heard anyt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't think I've ever heard anything less relevant to any investigation."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""C'mon, detective, he's the most re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, detective, he's the most repentant law official in the land. I don't mind."

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you. That's it -- for the re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you. That's it -- for the record."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""You kicked it down -- you tell me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You kicked it down -- you tell me."
fields.Alternate1: "You tell me, officer. I've been trying to open it. In case the Contamination gets to the roof and I have to move on. No luck."
fields.Alternate2: "You tell me, officer -- you kicked it down. I've been wondering myself but I'm... light of foot. Not a good door-kicker."

fields.Title: You: ""Nice room you've got here.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nice room you've got here."

fields.Title: You: ""Why here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why here?"

fields.Title: You: ""I do.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I do."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "You hear the scribbling of the lieu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear the scribbling of the lieutenant's pen.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""A peep hole? You mean like a hole..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A peep hole? You mean like a hole in the wall?"

fields.Title: You: ""Why do I feel like you've *won* he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why do I feel like you've *won* here?"

fields.Title: You: ""Yes. Why was it there?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Why was it there?"

fields.Title: You: ""The Hardie boys told us what reall..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Hardie boys told us what really happened."
fields.Alternate1: "Tell me what really happened, one more time."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "...then tears one out and hands it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...then tears one out and hands it to you. "We have questions that might help solve some gaps in our field autopsy. I'm sure my colleague has a few of his own while I take notes."

fields.Title: You: "Wouldn't it be, um... inappropriate..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wouldn't it be, um... inappropriate to linger?

fields.Title: Suggestion: "No one likes to talk about their di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one likes to talk about their dirty laundry and their empty bottles. Maybe if you phrase it emotionally...

fields.Title: You: ""I was undergoing a massive speed h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was undergoing a massive speed hangover. I needed to prop myself up."

fields.Title: You: ""It was confiscation.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was confiscation."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "No, no, don't listen to *the stiff*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, no, don't listen to *the stiff*. Be cool.

fields.Title: You: ""In my head it designates people wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In my head it designates people who abuse substances."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Very funky." She takes a drag, loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very funky." She takes a drag, looking you straight in the eye.

fields.Title: You: ""The collection includes NACRA -- a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The collection includes NACRA -- an opioid antagonist."

fields.Title: You: ""I have more questions about the de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have more questions about the deceased, but I need my partner here before I ask..."
